<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
The species (Fig. 7C) was previously known from East Africa and the Mascarenes (
<bibRefCitation author="Timdal, E" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="57 - 90" title="Further studies on African species of the lichen genus Phyllopsora (Lecanorales)." volume="77" year="2001">Timdal and Krog 2001</bibRefCitation>
). Although not sequenced, we here report it as new to Asia based on a specimen (Moberg 2750, UPS) from Sri Lanka (Suppl. material 2: Table S1). The species is the phylogenetic sister to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. parvifolia" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="parvifolia">P. parvifolia</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 1).
</paragraph>
